articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's October economic activity perked up as industrial output grew at a faster pace and retail sales growth beat expectations, an encouraging sign for an economy still showing significant pockets of weakness despite a flurry of support measures.
articles.title: China factory output, retail sales beat expectations in boost to economic recovery

articles.author: Christoph Steitz, Alexander Hübner
articles.description: Siemens Energy (ENR1n.DE) is reviewing the structure of Siemens Gamesa, it said on Wednesday, in a bid to return to profit the struggling wind division which caused a 4.6 billion euro ($5.0 billion) annual net loss for the group.
articles.title: Siemens Energy reviews structure of wind unit after $5 bln loss

articles.author: Michael Kahn, Anna Koper
articles.description: Central European defence companies are negotiating new deals to sell more weapons, military equipment and related services in Africa as they seek to poach customers looking for alternatives to Russia, companies and government officials say.
articles.title: Central Europe's defence companies spy African opportunity

articles.author: Leika Kihara
articles.description: The Bank of Japan has stepped up its drum beat of hawkish comments over the past week, in a series of communications that insiders say is priming markets for an end to negative interest rates, which could happen in the first few months of next year.
articles.title: BOJ's hawkish rhetoric signals chance negative rates may end soon

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The head of Germany's drug regulator BfArM is considering an export ban on Novo Nordisk's (NOVOb.CO) diabetes drug Ozempic, which is in high demand for its weight-loss benefits, to prevent a further worsening of a supply shortage.
articles.title: German drug regulator considering export ban on Ozempic

articles.author: Josh Ye
articles.description: TikTok owner ByteDance has been meeting up with potential buyers for a sale of its gaming unit Moonton Technology two years after it acquired the Shanghai-based studio in a deal that valued it at $4 billion, people familiar with the matter said.
articles.title: Exclusive: China's Bytedance is talking to likely buyers about gaming unit Moonton's sale-sources

articles.author: Richa Naidu, Aishwarya Venugopal
articles.description: Santa Claus may not have as much to give this year because hard up shoppers in Europe and the United States are prioritizing food and household staples, global toy makers and industry experts said.
articles.title: Santa's sleigh to be lighter as people buy fewer toys

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The Israeli military said it was carrying out an operation against Hamas in the Gaza Strip's Al Shifa hospital on Wednesday and urged all members of the militant group in the hospital to surrender.
articles.title: Israel raids Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden meets Chinese leader Xi Jinping for the first time in a year on Wednesday, for talks that may ease friction between the adversarial superpowers on military conflicts, drug-trafficking and artificial intelligence.
articles.title: Biden, Xi meet as US-China military, economic tensions grind on

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Emirates and Rolls-Royce (RR.L) sought to narrow differences over engine pricing on Wednesday as the Dubai Airshow entered a third day reeling from a public spat over engine performance and business terms that blocked a deal for Airbus A350-1000 jets.
articles.title: Airlines in last-minute talks to rescue Dubai Airshow deals
